'''''The Cheerful Squadron''''' ({{lang-it|Allegro squadrone}}, {{lang-fr|Les gaietés de l'escadron}}) is a 1954 Italian-French [[Comedy film|war-comedy film]] directed by [[Paolo Moffa]].<ref name="45-59">{{cite book|author1=Roberto Chiti |author2=Roberto Poppi |author3=Enrico Lancia |title=Dizionario del cinema italiano: I film|publisher=Gremese, 1991|isbn=8876055487}}</ref><ref name=Mereghetti>{{cite book|last=Paolo Mereghetti|title=Il Mereghetti|publisher=B.C. Dalai Editore, 2010|isbn=8860736269}}</ref>

== Cast ==

*[[Vittorio De Sica]]: the General 
*[[Daniel Gélin]]:  Frédéric d'Héricourt
*[[Paolo Stoppa]]: Maresciallo Flik
*[[Alberto Sordi]]: Vergisson
*[[Silvana Pampanini]]: Albertina 
*[[Charles Vanel]]: Hurluret
*[[Luigi Pavese]]: Capitano medico
*[[Riccardo Fellini]]: Bonaparte
*[[Memmo Carotenuto]]: Sergente maggiore
*[[Peter Trent]]: Lt. Moussent
*[[Giacomo Furia]]: Caporale
*[[Jean Richard]]: Laperrine
*[[Oreste Lionello]]

